This code chunk defines dictionaries for object management within a cluster client, including mappings between object names and their corresponding server-side controls, color data, offsets, priorities, and tagged objects. These dictionaries are used in the `ClusterClient` or related classes to synchronize object states and control mappings across distributed servers.

# A dictionary of objects that can be accessed by name
        self.objectMappings  = {}
        self.objectHasColor  = {}

        # a dictionary of name objects and the corresponding names of
        # objects they are to control on the server side
        self.controlMappings = {}
        self.controlOffsets  = {}
        self.taggedObjects   = {}
        self.controlPriorities = {}
        self.sortedControlMappings = []
